Lera. find any device near her.

1027
01:15:34.730 --> 01:15:39.550
There will still be rotation.
You just have to wait a little.

1028
01:15:39.580 --> 01:15:41.490
How are you?

1029
01:15:41.510 --> 01:15:44.370
Fine.

1030
01:15:44.400 --> 01:15:45.640
Quality.

1031
01:15:45.670 --> 01:15:48.280
I thought the
connection was down.

1032
01:15:48.300 --> 01:15:50.900
- Hello. huh?
- Pass the phone to Lera.

1033
01:15:50.920 --> 01:15:52.200
And who are you?

1034
01:15:52.230 --> 01:15:54.700
Boy. give Lera the phone.

1035
01:15:54.730 --> 01:15:58.600
Yes. hello. You
actually call my phone.

1036
01:15:58.620 --> 01:16:04.470
See the camera on the pole?

1037
01:16:04.500 --> 01:16:08.050
In short. Terentiev Mikhail Vasilievich.
graduate of boarding school No. 14.

1038
01:16:08.070 --> 01:16:11.260
registered for petty
hooliganism. Give Lera the phone.

1039
01:16:11.290 --> 01:16:13.170
Be kind.

1040
01:16:13.200 --> 01:16:14.710
Are you a cop or what?

1041
01:16:14.740 --> 01:16:16.000
No. I'm an astronaut. Misha.

1042
01:16:16.020 --> 01:16:19.770
I can see everything from
above. you know that. understand?

1043
01:16:19.790 --> 01:16:21.400
- Your father?
- Yes.

1044
01:16:21.420 --> 01:16:23.490
- Hi Dad.
- Lera. you need to leave.

1045
01:16:23.520 --> 01:16:26.890
- Right now.
- What?

1046
01:16:26.920 --> 01:16:29.730
- And the helicopter?
- There will be no helicopter.

1047
01:16:29.750 --> 01:16:33.640
Do you see the tanker? There was an
explosion recently. Detonated small tank.

1048
01:16:33.670 --> 01:16:34.970
Now there is a
fire in the holds.

1049
01:16:35.000 --> 01:16:37.800
If the fire gets close
to the main tanks.

1050
01:16:37.820 --> 01:16:43.360
the explosion will demolish
half the city. you understand?

1051
01:16:43.380 --> 01:16:47.260
Yes. I understood. I'll warn
people then. and you tell...

1052
01:16:47.280 --> 01:16:49.870
- Lera. stop.
- Rescuers.

1053
01:16:49.900 --> 01:16:52.170
Listen to me.

1054
01:16:52.200 --> 01:16:54.270
I calculated everything.

1055
01:16:54.300 --> 01:16:56.720
Rescuers are far away.
they won't make it in time.

1056
01:16:56.750 --> 01:16:58.440
People won't take
your word for it.

1057
01:16:58.470 --> 01:17:01.760
But even if they believe. panic
will begin. you will just lose time.

1058
01:17:01.790 --> 01:17:04.910
In general. such ships have
a fire extinguishing system.

1059
01:17:04.940 --> 01:17:06.660
I've entered a sailor.

1060
01:17:06.690 --> 01:17:10.430
Arabov. you can connect to
everything. so connect to this system.

1061
01:17:10.450 --> 01:17:13.300
Lera. I tried. the
old-style system.

1062
01:17:13.320 --> 01:17:15.450
There's no remote
control. you know

1063
01:17:15.470 --> 01:17:18.400
everything is done by hand. and there
is simply no one there to do it manually.

1064
01:17:18.420 --> 01:17:20.080
So Lera. there is
only one way out.

1065
01:17:20.100 --> 01:17:22.480
Run and hide as far as possible.

1066
01:17:22.510 --> 01:17:24.490
Mira will build a path
to the nearest bunker.

1067
01:17:24.510 --> 01:17:28.810
It is safe there.
I will guide you.

1068
01:17:28.830 --> 01:17:31.380
Run?

1069
01:17:31.410 --> 01:17:34.080
And hide as far as possible?

1070
01:17:34.110 --> 01:17:42.110
Well. that is. how did
you do it then. right?

1071
01:17:44.340 --> 01:17:50.120
Let's discuss
this later. please.

1072
01:17:50.150 --> 01:17:54.570
You said the
rescuers won't make it.

1073
01:17:54.590 --> 01:17:57.410
Well. we are here.

1074
01:17:57.430 --> 01:17:59.840
Quite near.

1075
01:17:59.860 --> 01:18:05.090
So we can activate this
system ourselves. Yes. Misha?

1076
01:18:05.100 --> 01:18:06.320
Huh?

1077
01:18:06.340 --> 01:18:08.280
Listen.

1078
01:18:08.310 --> 01:18:09.970
What?

1079
01:18:10.000 --> 01:18:12.220
Have you lost your
mind or something. Lera?

1080
01:18:12.250 --> 01:18:14.640
Will you help us?

1081
01:18:14.670 --> 01:18:17.440
So you want to go
and put it out yourself?

1082
01:18:17.460 --> 01:18:20.730
Did I understand you correctly?

1083
01:18:20.760 --> 01:18:24.460
Does that mean I can't
count on your help?

1084
01:18:24.480 --> 01:18:25.680
Did I understand correctly?

1085
01:18:25.700 --> 01:18:28.260
Lera. what are
you talking about?

1086
01:18:28.280 --> 01:18:30.360
You can't look at a lit match.

1087
01:18:30.390 --> 01:18:32.590
Do you want to go
through a burning tanker?

1088
01:18:32.620 --> 01:18:35.300
Yes. who do you think you
are there. huh? Superhero?

1089
01:18:35.320 --> 01:18:39.160
No. I'm not a superhero. I'm a
girl with special needs. remember?

1090
01:18:39.180 --> 01:18:42.720
Uh-uh. it was actually a gift.

1091
01:18:42.740 --> 01:18:43.830
From grandma.

1092
01:18:43.860 --> 01:18:47.100
Lera. Lera.

1093
01:18:47.110 --> 01:18:49.070
Crap.

1094
01:18:49.100 --> 01:18:52.966
- How do we get on the tanker?
- I thought you were kidding.

1095
01:18:55.890 --> 01:18:57.966
Are you kidding?

1096
01:19:10.590 --> 01:19:12.590
The doctor said a slight
concussion. Everything will be fine.

1097
01:19:12.610 --> 01:19:14.330
Carefully. Hot.

1098
01:19:14.350 --> 01:19:16.333
Listen.

1099
01:19:22.090 --> 01:19:25.200
Hello.

1100
01:19:25.220 --> 01:19:26.979
Sveta. forgive me.

1101
01:19:31.300 --> 01:19:35.720
I promised to
help Lera. but... I...

1102
01:19:35.750 --> 01:19:40.740
What's wrong with
her. where is she?

1103
01:19:40.770 --> 01:19:43.270
I don't know.

1104
01:19:43.290 --> 01:19:48.000
How are you... You promised me.

1105
01:19:48.020 --> 01:19:53.979
You... Forgive me. Sveta.

1106
01:19:55.100 --> 01:20:00.640
I couldn't then and now I can't.

1107
01:20:00.660 --> 01:20:05.979
Why did you open the door
yourself? Who are the instructions for?

1108
01:20:09.350 --> 01:20:12.500
Lera? Lera?

1109
01:20:12.530 --> 01:20:17.979
What were you doing here?
What were you doing here?

1110
01:20:23.470 --> 01:20:27.280
How can I help her now if

1111
01:20:27.300 --> 01:20:30.170
then I was so close to her

1112
01:20:30.200 --> 01:20:34.870
and still couldn't do anything.

1113
01:20:34.890 --> 01:20:41.870
You was right.

1114
01:20:41.900 --> 01:20:45.200
She's just a weakling.

1115
01:20:45.230 --> 01:20:46.780
Valera. no.

1116
01:20:46.810 --> 01:20:49.620
Please don't say that.

1117
01:20:49.650 --> 01:20:53.650
I speak as it is.

1118
01:20:53.680 --> 01:20:58.166
You... Are you hungry there?

1119
01:21:00.830 --> 01:21:07.160
Valera. are you hungry there?

1120
01:21:07.180 --> 01:21:10.080
Well. there is litte.

1121
01:21:10.090 --> 01:21:13.000
Well. of course. if
you're hungry there...

1122
01:21:13.020 --> 01:21:14.190
So this is a guard in general.

1123
01:21:14.220 --> 01:21:16.610
You open there for yourself some

1124
01:21:16.630 --> 01:21:18.600
astronaut breakfast.

1125
01:21:23.920 --> 01:21:26.220
I believe in you.

1126
01:21:26.240 --> 01:21:27.800
Do you hear?

1127
01:21:31.520 --> 01:21:35.950
If someone can save
our daughter now.

1128
01:21:35.970 --> 01:21:37.600
it's only you.

1129
01:21:42.290 --> 01:21:46.840
You just stay with her. okay?

1130
01:21:46.850 --> 01:21:49.100
Just stay close to her.

1131
01:22:30.600 --> 01:22:32.800
Arabova. chore to tremble. huh?

1132
01:22:32.820 --> 01:22:34.860
The boat is shaking
because of you.

1133
01:22:34.880 --> 01:22:38.830
- Frozen. right?
- Not frozen.

1134
01:22:38.850 --> 01:22:42.020
Maybe on the oars?
Okay. I'm kidding.

1135
01:22:42.050 --> 01:22:44.960
You will warm up on the tanker.

1136
01:22:44.980 --> 01:22:46.810
Terentiev. are
you a human at all?

1137
01:22:46.830 --> 01:22:49.220
What are you doing as a joke?

1138
01:22:49.240 --> 01:22:50.400
Habit.

1139
01:22:50.420 --> 01:22:53.480
Ah. How long have
you had this habit?

1140
01:22:53.510 --> 01:22:54.990
With 13.

1141
01:22:55.020 --> 01:22:59.400
Then I decided to joke with a
firecracker. the joke came out!

1142
01:23:01.200 --> 01:23:07.000
I've been having fun ever since.

1143
01:23:07.020 --> 01:23:12.100
I saw burns when we put
Yegor into the helicopter.

1144
01:23:12.130 --> 01:23:13.540
Are you ashamed of them?

1145
01:23:13.560 --> 01:23:14.930
No. I'm proud of them.

1146
01:23:14.950 --> 01:23:16.690
What?

1147
01:23:16.720 --> 01:23:19.250
I would be proud.

1148
01:23:19.280 --> 01:23:22.666
Yes? But would you be
proud of this ugliness too?

1149
01:23:27.320 --> 01:23:29.780
I don't see any ugliness.

1150
01:23:29.810 --> 01:23:31.740
I see a person in front of me

1151
01:23:31.760 --> 01:23:35.230
who survived the pain. was able
to cope with it and remained a human.

1152
01:23:35.260 --> 01:23:39.900
That's why. yes.
I would be proud.

1153
01:24:10.850 --> 01:24:12.933
Come on. what.

1154
01:24:32.150 --> 01:24:33.430
Well. where next?

1155
01:24:33.460 --> 01:24:36.090
In terms of? You were a sailor.

1156
01:24:36.100 --> 01:24:39.200
- Ah. So I did not.
- What?

1157
01:24:39.220 --> 01:24:42.310
Calm down. we'll figure it out.

1158
01:24:42.340 --> 01:24:45.480
Let's go to. You just
have to follow the signs.

1159
01:24:45.500 --> 01:24:47.979
On the courts. everything
is usually signed.

1160
01:24:56.979 --> 01:24:59.979
Don't slow down. let's go.

1161
01:25:12.460 --> 01:25:14.979
Where?

1162
01:25:17.090 --> 01:25:18.900
There.

1163
01:25:28.530 --> 01:25:30.920
Hold on. Hold on.

1164
01:25:30.940 --> 01:25:32.979
Here.

1165
01:25:37.620 --> 01:25:37.910
What?

1166
01:25:37.920 --> 01:25:40.740
Don't touch anything
here. everything is hot here.

1167
01:25:40.770 --> 01:25:41.979
Where?

1168
01:25:45.120 --> 01:25:47.233
- Where?
- Here.

1169
01:25:54.330 --> 01:25:56.240
Straight up.

1170
01:25:56.270 --> 01:25:59.979
I told you not to
touch anything.

1171
01:26:01.960 --> 01:26:03.900
Here.

1172
01:26:19.770 --> 01:26:20.970
What?

1173
01:26:21.000 --> 01:26:23.230
Calm down. calm down. Everything
is fine. Arabov. what are you doing?

1174
01:26:23.250 --> 01:26:25.220
Arabov. look at me.

1175
01:26:25.250 --> 01:26:27.980
I'll go look for a plan. you
sit with a toy. Understood?

1176
01:26:28.000 --> 01:26:30.580
- This is not a toy.
- Yes? Yes.

1177
01:26:30.600 --> 01:26:32.020
- It's not a toy.
- Yes Yes Yes.

1178
01:26:32.050 --> 01:26:34.640
- It's a baby monitor.
- Dad and I are talking with it.

1179
01:26:34.660 --> 01:26:40.020
- With dad on the baby monitor.
- I understood you. she just broke down.

1180
01:26:40.040 --> 01:26:42.050
Let's see.

1181
01:26:42.080 --> 01:26:44.100
Let's see. let's see.

1182
01:26:53.720 --> 01:26:56.120
I love you.

1183
01:26:56.140 --> 01:26:58.950
Communication device available.

1184
01:26:58.970 --> 01:27:02.730
So. Get in touch
with Lera. quickly.

1185
01:27:02.750 --> 01:27:04.830
Lera.

1186
01:27:04.850 --> 01:27:06.040
Misha. where is she?

1187
01:27:06.070 --> 01:27:08.260
Arabov. Again. I
didn't listen to you.

1188
01:27:08.290 --> 01:27:10.540
Now it's not about
that. We'll discuss later.

1189
01:27:10.570 --> 01:27:14.110
So yes. There are fires everywhere on your
level. you can't get through here anymore.

1190
01:27:14.140 --> 01:27:16.390
You need to go down to the
engine room. this is the only way out.

1191
01:27:16.410 --> 01:27:19.000
Look for a hatch in the floor and get
down. Do you hear me? Get down quickly.

1192
01:27:19.030 --> 01:27:21.310
So. Luke in the floor.

1193
01:27:21.340 --> 01:27:22.980
This?

1194
01:27:23.000 --> 01:27:25.770
No Another. Search.
There must be a hatch.

1195
01:27:25.790 --> 01:27:28.150
There. Here.

1196
01:27:28.180 --> 01:27:30.010
Let's go. Let's go. Let's go.

1197
01:27:30.030 --> 01:27:31.850
Yes. it.

1198
01:27:31.870 --> 01:27:34.270
Get down. quickly.

1199
01:27:34.300 --> 01:27:36.670
Your dad is really cool.

1200
01:27:36.700 --> 01:27:38.979
But the family is wild.

1201
01:27:48.190 --> 01:27:50.979
There along the corridor.
There will be a door.

1202
01:27:56.750 --> 01:27:59.979
Faster. Lera. faster. The
walls were almost burned out.

1203
01:28:05.500 --> 01:28:08.979
Misha. there is a sealed
door ahead. close it.

1204
01:28:11.950 --> 01:28:16.420
On top of the steering
wheel. seal the compartment.

1205
01:28:16.440 --> 01:28:18.590
Come on. come on.

1206
01:28:18.610 --> 01:28:22.150
Let's go.

1207
01:28:22.160 --> 01:28:30.170
Calm down. daughter. You
succeed. Everything is fine.

1208
01:28:31.370 --> 01:28:32.670
Yes.

1209
01:28:32.690 --> 01:28:33.740
Well done.

1210
01:28:33.770 --> 01:28:35.430
- How are you?
- Fine.

1211
01:28:35.450 --> 01:28:37.010
See the engines now?

1212
01:28:37.040 --> 01:28:40.190
At the end of the
passage is a room.

1213
01:28:40.220 --> 01:28:41.390
- Go ahead. Arabova.
- Here.

1214
01:28:41.410 --> 01:28:42.900
Come on. come on. come on.

1215
01:28:42.920 --> 01:28:44.979
Get down. run forward. Faster.

1216
01:28:51.900 --> 01:28:54.800
- Closer. - Where to go?
- Ladder.

1217
01:28:59.970 --> 01:29:01.800
Higher.

1218
01:29:06.830 --> 01:29:09.110
Higher. higher. higher.

1219
01:29:09.130 --> 01:29:10.780
Come on. come on. come on.

1220
01:29:10.810 --> 01:29:12.440
On this level. the
second door on the left.

1221
01:29:12.460 --> 01:29:15.770
It's here.

1222
01:29:15.790 --> 01:29:16.890
Quickly inside.

1223
01:29:16.920 --> 01:29:21.370
Get away. get away.

1224
01:29:21.400 --> 01:29:23.070
Great. you are right there.

1225
01:29:23.090 --> 01:29:24.590
So. now the control panel.

1226
01:29:24.620 --> 01:29:26.979
Yes. everything seems
to be simple here.

1227
01:29:31.170 --> 01:29:33.020
Stop. Lera. there's
something wrong here.

1228
01:29:33.040 --> 01:29:34.860
Damn. that means
the power went out.

1229
01:29:34.890 --> 01:29:36.730
Misha. you have to do it
manually. There's a manual

1230
01:29:36.760 --> 01:29:38.520
compartment at the end
of the room. do you hear?

1231
01:29:38.540 --> 01:29:40.700
Stay here. I'm right now.

1232
01:29:40.730 --> 01:29:44.979
Misha. just don't come in right
away. check the temperature.

1233
01:29:50.840 --> 01:29:52.940
Lera. Lera. reception.

1234
01:29:52.960 --> 01:29:55.500
Lera. Lera.

1235
01:29:55.530 --> 01:29:59.266
Misha! Misha. Misha. Misha!

1236
01:30:04.980 --> 01:30:07.533
Dad! Dad!

1237
01:30:09.990 --> 01:30:14.979
Quiet. quiet. quiet. Calm down.
Now. now I'll think of something.

1238
01:30:21.580 --> 01:30:23.650
Lera. reception.

1239
01:30:23.680 --> 01:30:24.770
Mira. what's the matter?

1240
01:30:24.800 --> 01:30:27.900
Contact with the batteries in the
laboratory compartment has been lost.

1241
01:30:27.920 --> 01:30:30.550
- The system is in hibernation mode.
- Just not now.

1242
01:30:30.570 --> 01:30:32.710
Not now. Mira.

1243
01:30:32.720 --> 01:30:36.170
Turn off everything you
can. All life support systems.

1244
01:30:36.190 --> 01:30:42.140
Just give me back the link.

1245
01:30:42.170 --> 01:30:44.220
Power is not enough.

1246
01:30:44.250 --> 01:30:46.930
Dear. dear. I need a connection
with Lera. you understand?

1247
01:30:46.950 --> 01:30:49.740
Need. need.
otherwise it's pointless.

1248
01:30:49.770 --> 01:30:53.780
Establishing a connection is possible
only when a search system is connected

1249
01:30:53.810 --> 01:30:55.350
to the station's
active power source.

1250
01:30:55.370 --> 01:30:57.450
What? What is another
active source of energy?

1251
01:30:57.480 --> 01:31:01.420
The power supply of the central
data storage of the voice assistant.

1252
01:31:01.450 --> 01:31:08.380
Mira. so use urgently. huh?

1253
01:31:11.500 --> 01:31:12.760
Mira.

1254
01:31:12.790 --> 01:31:14.300
Arabov flight engineer.

1255
01:31:14.330 --> 01:31:17.790
Unlike a human. I
can't turn myself off.

1256
01:31:17.820 --> 01:31:23.670
You will have to perform
this action manually.

1257
01:31:23.700 --> 01:31:26.860
Do you know why
your name is Mira?

1258
01:31:26.880 --> 01:31:29.980
My full name is the voice
assistant of personnel

1259
01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:32.270
orbital station 'MIR A'.

1260
01:31:32.290 --> 01:31:35.210
Mira is a double star.

1261
01:31:35.240 --> 01:31:39.630
One big strong another small but

1262
01:31:39.650 --> 01:31:41.790
very bright.

1263
01:31:41.810 --> 01:31:44.410
The little one
covers the big one.

1264
01:31:44.430 --> 01:31:48.360
The big one
protects the little one.

1265
01:31:48.390 --> 01:31:52.710
And without each other. their
existence will simply lose its meaning.

1266
01:31:52.730 --> 01:31:54.370
A beautiful metaphor.

1267
01:31:54.390 --> 01:31:56.260
I wonder who invented it?

1268
01:31:56.290 --> 01:31:57.220
Huh?

1269
01:31:57.240 --> 01:32:03.580
It was a rhetorical question.

1270
01:32:03.610 --> 01:32:06.210
Farewell. flight
engineer Arabov.

1271
01:32:06.230 --> 01:32:07.966
Farewell. Mira.

1272
01:32:32.720 --> 01:32:35.450
Dad. dad. please. dad.

1273
01:32:35.480 --> 01:32:37.820
Lera. Lera. Lera. calm down.

1274
01:32:37.850 --> 01:32:39.740
Why didn't you answer me?

1275
01:32:39.760 --> 01:32:42.170
Calm down. what about Misha?

1276
01:32:42.190 --> 01:32:44.010
